<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="666">Major: relatively flat profile of the promesonotum in dorsal-oblique view; eye set well forward so that its anterior margin is the same distance from the anterior genal border as the Eye Length; small, obtuse-angulate mesonotal convexity; and smooth, shiny occiput, postpetiolar node, and first gastral tergite.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="666">Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 1.06, HL 1.06, SL 0.62, EL 0.18, PW 0.48. Paratype minor: HW 0.60, HL 0.60, SL 0.60, EL 0.12, PW 0.34.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="666">color Major: head dark reddish yellow, rest of body light reddish brown, legs dark yellow. Minor: concolorous dark yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="666">Range Known from only two collections at the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="666">biology Found by Longino (1997) nesting in epiphyte clumps in wet forest.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
